President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Rebecca F. Dye for the position of Commissioner of the Federal Maritime Commission. Dye has previously served as a Federal Maritime Commissioner, a commissioned officer and attorney in the United States Coast Guard, and as a law instructor at the U.S. Coast Guard Academy. She has also worked as an attorney with the U.S. Maritime Administration and served as Minority Counsel for the Committee on Merchant Marine and Fisheries in the U.S. House of Representatives. Dye has extensive experience in handling legislative issues related to international ocean shipping, maritime safety, and law enforcement. She graduated from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 1974 and earned a law degree from the University of North Carolina in 1977.